snippet: Missy Franklin won the 200 backstroke at the world championships, tying the record for most titles by a woman at the meet, and Katie Ledecky set a second world record, in the 800 freestyle.
abstract: Missy Franklin wins 200-meter backstroke for her fifth golf medal at swimming world championships.
lead_paragraph: Missy Franklin won the 200 backstroke at the world championships, tying the record for most titles by a woman at the meet, and Katie Ledecky set a second world record, in the 800 freestyle.

headline.main: 5th Gold for Franklin and 4th for Ledecky at Swimming Worlds
